(* Test executable basis: the treap library (which pulls in the vendored
   sml-prng generators) plus the harness, helpers, and per-feature suites.

   sml-check is a TEST-only dependency (the library's production dependency
   is only sml-prng, pulled in unwrapped by ../src/treap.mlb so consumers can
   name SplitMix64 directly). Include order for the flat Poly/ML `use` model
   (tools/polybuild): sml-prng -> sml-test (check.sig references Test.test in
   its toTest bridge) -> sml-check -> our own Harness -> the library under
   test -> the suites -> entry/main shims. This creates a second, independent
   copy of the Prng/SplitMix64 structures used only by Check; MLB scopes each
   imported .mlb file's basis from its own contents, so ../src/treap.mlb's
   own (self-contained) import of sml-prng is unaffected, and IntTreap /
   StringTreap (already fully instantiated inside treap.sml) never cross
   the two instances. *)
$(SML_LIB)/basis/basis.mlb

../lib/github.com/sjqtentacles/sml-prng/prng.sig
../lib/github.com/sjqtentacles/sml-prng/prng.sml
../lib/github.com/sjqtentacles/sml-test/test.sig
../lib/github.com/sjqtentacles/sml-test/test.sml
../lib/github.com/sjqtentacles/sml-check/check.sig
../lib/github.com/sjqtentacles/sml-check/check.sml

../src/treap.mlb

harness.sml
support.sml
test_invariants.sml
test_splitmerge.sml
test_determinism.sml
test_properties.sml
entry.sml
main.sml
